<subSubSection id="5025C8EDFE74F3B787333ABA474A4ABC" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="27A734211AC3A8A5D57F0C223F180BB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName id="1997702783BF8223C260E3ECD25C33BA" authority="Enderlein, 1912" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Lichtwardtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lichtwardtia ziczac" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziczac">Lichtwardtia ziczac</taxonomicName>
(Wiedemann, 1824) sensu Zhang, Masunaga &amp; Yang, 2009: 199, figs 11-14. Re-description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3CC1B6554AD5EC3A3710D26C6F21CA88" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5B4F4E8048E76391319B1BD021946413" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19B170060DB59E996AFA4B94D446F279" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
This species is dedicated to Dr. Lili Zhang of the IOZ Museum in Beijing who re-described and illustrated 
<taxonomicName id="1E9F711449B667662100556961297F81" authority="Enderlein, 1912" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Lichtwardtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lichtwardtia ziczac" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziczac">Lichtwardtia ziczac</taxonomicName>
(Wiedemann) for the first time with detailed drawings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="246D7DA921F7745E4473530C34D3F180" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="33A105A3DF298AF2A40DB3DA5ABB2F23" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="80EE3FFFC83EF6101CE8B9BD9B6C02D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Costa without swelling. Hypandrium with a large brown dorsal preapical tooth. Phallus smooth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3422F23D8A2454E342AB5D94D417D5D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC3AA018EAEAED535158761AC6D3D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="35E4B6FDBBBC29C941FAAE6D3C8DE5D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
For a full description we refer to 
<bibRefCitation id="6F013FAC43976D5054BCADE07B0F47E7" author="Zhang, L" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" pagination="197 - 203" title="Species of Lichtwardtia from China (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3157/061.135.0208" volume="135" year="2009">Zhang et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="910B87A2A5CC4B211E7ED4A0E2393AB5" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="comments">
<paragraph id="FA7932AF7342168FDDCF4B8ECF49920A" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="770932D9E57B79F289CBE9F482132133" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
In having the cross veins clouded, 
<taxonomicName id="93077DE77A5F465B15F9F179D1934647" authority="Enderlein, 1912" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Lichtwardtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lichtwardtia ziczac" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziczac">Lichtwardtia ziczac</taxonomicName>
(Wiedemann) is distinctly different from 
<taxonomicName id="E5781DEE9F367217638F0BCB1C50398D" genus="L." lsidName="L. ziczac" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" rank="species" species="ziczac">L. ziczac</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="8AB116011E3EF04EFC430A4A6BE60700" author="Zhang, L" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" pagination="197 - 203" title="Species of Lichtwardtia from China (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3157/061.135.0208" volume="135" year="2009">Zhang et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
and therefore we give a new name 
<taxonomicName id="0A9BDC2F0AC9D5C396A24A131C19B617" authority="Enderlein, 1912" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Lichtwardtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lichtwardtia zhangae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhangae">Lichtwardtia zhangae</taxonomicName>
sp. n. to the species that she (re-) described from Bali. It is very closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="FE98147130608DD73D1A46B69854BDFE" genus="L." lsidName="L. polychroma" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" rank="species" species="polychroma">L. polychroma</taxonomicName>
from Sri Lanka and differs in the lacking of a swelling of the costa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D7ED0D13A36D9037CC6F532CEDD65D38" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BB05A4CE0D6177D0FFD712E1107A99ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B428FBF6789F7D26825E9D3EC309C9F" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Bali (Indonesia).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
